abstract: Albany Republicans seem to like watching Mayor Bill de Blasio squirm.
snippet: Albany Republicans seem to like watching Mayor Bill de Blasio squirm.
lead_paragraph: Here we are with yet another remake of a movie that wasn’t particularly watchable the first time around: What price will New York State Senate Republicans exact to extend the mayor’s control over New York City’s public schools — and for how long a stretch? With the Legislature hoping to close shop on Wednesday, and the mayor’s present authority expiring June 30, the question is loaded with urgency and anxiety.

headline_main: Tired of the Suspense on Mayoral Control of Schools
headline_print_headline: Suspense on Mayoral Control of Schools, Again

abstract: As the legislative calendar nears an end, officials are resisting the use of the issue as a bargaining chip.
snippet: As the legislative calendar nears an end, officials are resisting the use of the issue as a bargaining chip.
lead_paragraph: For the last two years, the negotiation over mayoral control for New York City schools resembled most deals in Albany: a back-room, last-minute give-and-take involving legislative concessions from Assembly Democrats and Senate Republicans.

headline_main: New York City Officials Raise Pressure Over Mayoral Control of Schools
headline_print_headline: City Officials Make Push for Mayoral School Control

abstract: Dire warnings from the de Blasio administration notwithstanding, the last time the law on mayoral authority was allowed to expire, chaos didn’t reign.
snippet: Dire warnings from the de Blasio administration notwithstanding, the last time the law on mayoral authority was allowed to expire, chaos didn’t reign.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio has suggested that if the Legislature leaves Albany on Wednesday without renewing mayoral control of schools, which is set to lapse on July 1, the city’s education system will immediately descend into chaos.

headline_main: New York City Pensions Are Still in Crisis
byline_original: By MARY WILLIAMS WALSH and KARL RUSSELL

abstract: The company is joining other oil companies and corporate giants to endorse a plan from the Climate Leadership Council to tax fossil fuels and pay the dividends to taxpayers.
snippet: The company is joining other oil companies and corporate giants to endorse a plan from the Climate Leadership Council to tax fossil fuels and pay the dividends to taxpayers.
lead_paragraph: Exxon Mobil, other oil companies and a number of other corporate giants announced on Tuesday that they are supporting a plan to tax carbon emissions that was put forth this year by a group of Republican elder statesmen.

abstract: Without an extension from the State Legislature, the power that the mayor has to choose the city school chancellor and set educational policy will expire at the end of June.
snippet: Without an extension from the State Legislature, the power that the mayor has to choose the city school chancellor and set educational policy will expire at the end of June.
lead_paragraph: There’s still not much love in Albany for Mayor Bill de Blasio. Hoping to win a last-minute deal in the Legislature to extend mayoral control over city schools, he telephoned the leader of the Republicans in the State Senate, John J. Flanagan, on Monday morning.

abstract: Corporate giants once had all-powerful chiefs with domains to match. But activist investors and technological change are remaking the executive suite.
snippet: Corporate giants once had all-powerful chiefs with domains to match. But activist investors and technological change are remaking the executive suite.
lead_paragraph: FAIRFIELD, Conn. — They bestrode the business world, or at least the suburban corporate campus, like a colossus.

headline_main: The Decline of the Baronial C.E.O.

abstract: John Mackey wanted to fight off the activist investors attacking Whole Foods. He found a savior in Amazon, a company blamed for laying waste to retailers.
snippet: John Mackey wanted to fight off the activist investors attacking Whole Foods. He found a savior in Amazon, a company blamed for laying waste to retailers.
lead_paragraph: Since John Mackey co-founded a precursor to Whole Foods in 1978, he has taken a hands-on management approach to the organic grocery chain. He personally oversaw each step of its national expansion. During a takeover battle 10 years ago, Mr. Mackey used a pseudonym to write anonymous blog posts attacking a competitor.

abstract: The American unit that makes Butterfingers, Crunch bars and Gobstoppers could be worth as much as $3 billion in a sale.
snippet: The American unit that makes Butterfingers, Crunch bars and Gobstoppers could be worth as much as $3 billion in a sale.
lead_paragraph: It seems Americans are losing their collective sweet tooth: Nestlé is considering selling less candy in the United States.
